        <div class="row g-5 row-cols-1 row-cols-lg-2">
            <div class="col order-last order-lg-first">
                <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold lh-1 mb-3 app-name">Project Palindrome: A coding project</h1>
                <h4 class="lead">
                    The goal of this project is to input a string and use a function to check if it is a palindrome.
                    A palindrome is a word or phrase that reads the same backward and forward. When palindromes are the length of a sentence, they ignore capitalization, punctuation, and word boundaries.
                </h4>
